 {"id":"bd-pm-epic","title":"PORT: /proc/self/maps line parser to core::proc_maps","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:05:20.017352Z","description":"Two abi files duplicate /proc/self/maps line parsing: host_resolve.rs::parse_maps_line (~25 lines, full parse with libc.so + perms + offset filters) and pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range (~7 lines, just the start-end address pair). Lift both into core::proc_maps with a shared MapsEntry struct + parse_maps_line, then rewire each abi caller to apply its specific filter on the borrowed result.","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","close_reason":"Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. Net effect: ~32 lines of duplicated /proc/self/maps parsing across two abi files (host_resolve.rs + pthread_abi.rs) replaced by a single ~95-line core::proc_maps module with 20 isolation-tested cases. The full MapsEntry view is now reachable from any other caller that wants address/perms/offset/dev/inode/path beyond just the start-end range."}
 {"id":"bd-pm-1","title":"PORT: proc_maps sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::proc_maps module","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-pm-epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:05:20.017352Z","description":"Add crates/frankenlibc-core/src/proc_maps/mod.rs with MapsEntry { start: usize, end: usize, perms: &str, offset: u64, dev: &str, inode: u64, path: Option<&str> }; parse_maps_line(line: &str) -> Option<MapsEntry>; parse_maps_range(line: &str) -> Option<(usize, usize)> as a thin shortcut over the start-end portion of the first whitespace-separated field. Tests cover: typical mapped library line with path, anonymous mapping (no path), VDSO/heap/stack named regions, malformed range fields, lines with extra trailing whitespace, hex parsing of large addresses (i.e., 64-bit), permission string variants (r--p, rw-p, r-xp, ---p).","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","close_reason":"Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/proc_maps/mod.rs with: MapsEntry<a> { start, end, perms, offset, dev, inode, path } as a borrowed view of one /proc/<pid>/maps line; parse_maps_line(line) -> Option<MapsEntry> handling typical mapped-library lines, anonymous mappings, pseudo-named regions ([stack]/[heap]/[vdso]/[vvar]), high 64-bit kernel addresses, all permission-string variants, EOL stripping, and rejecting truncated/malformed/extra-token lines; parse_maps_range(line) shortcut for callers that only need the start-end pair. 20 unit tests (13 parse_maps_line + 7 parse_maps_range) cover all the above cases plus a property test that range matches start/end of full parse."}
 {"id":"bd-pm-2","title":"PORT: proc_maps sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi callers","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-pm-epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:05:20.017352Z","description":"Replace inline parse_maps_line in host_resolve.rs with a call to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_line, then apply the libc.so + r--p + offset==0 filter on the returned MapsEntry. Replace pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range with a call to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_range. Verify both abi tests still pass.","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","close_reason":"host_resolve.rs::parse_maps_line shrinks from ~25 to ~16 lines: it now delegates to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_line, then applies the libc.so + r--p + offset==0 filter on the returned MapsEntry. pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range becomes a 1-line forwarder. Both abi callers retain their specific filtering / output-shape logic at the boundary. 173/173 abi lib tests pass."}
+{"id":"bd-xn6p8","title":"FUZZ: mount/umount/umount2 + fs* family structure-aware harness","description":"crates/frankenlibc-fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_mount.rs. Targets mount/umount/umount2 and the new mount API (fsopen/fsmount/fsconfig/fspick/open_tree/move_mount/mount_setattr). Covers null-pointer, fuzz-fsname, dirfd variation. Argument validation surface fully exercised independent of root privilege.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cc-libc","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:50:00.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-libc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:55:00.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:55:00.000000000Z","close_reason":"Verified fuzz_mount.rs covers mount/umount2/fsopen/fsmount/fsconfig/fspick/open_tree/move_mount/mount_setattr. 11.73M runs at 97K exec/s over 120s, no crashes. Pre-shipped harness verified end-to-end with rch (CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_target_libc_cc_xn6p8).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
